text:
"at 14, a grown man followed me home and tried to push my house door open. that is the true experience of a moroccan girl yet my stories aren't even as bad as it gets. must i speak of the girls that were raped and forced to marry their rapists? must i speak of the girls that were raped, murdered and decapitated? must i speak of the women who are abused and beaten by their husbands? must i speak of the women that are raped by their husbands but forced to believe that it is okay just because they are their husbands? must i speak of the young girls that are forced to marry men 4 times their ages by their parents? must i speak of the young maids that are regularly beaten by their bosses and forced to give their hard earned money to parents that don't care about them? must i speak of the young girls that are kidnapped and raped on their way to school?" - manar from #morocco

read her full interview at girltable.com/gtstoryproject

text:
tenéis mis ojos para leeros.
mis oídos para escucharos.
mis manos para ayudaros.
mi corazón entregado a la causa.
mi cabeza pensando en vosotras.

no estáis solas. 
ante el primer signo de violencia machista pedid ayuda. hay muchas feministas que estamos dispuestas a acompañaros en vuestra lucha. de corazón, nuestra prioridad es poder ayudaros a vosotras primero. nuestro objetivo terminar con el patriarcado. 
si estás de acuerdo y quieres ofrecer tu ayuda a otras mujeres en situaciones de riesgo, comparte el mensaje. podemos lograr hacerlas sentir que no están solas, estamos todas a su lado estén dónde estén para ofrecerles nuestra mano. juntas somos más fuertes. 
pd: se busca el nombre de la autora de la ilustración.

text: a rare and tasty treat from croatia: bačić cetinka 2016. cetinka is a grape variety native to korčula island in dalmatia, where it is sparsely cultivated and overshadowed by the more popular pošip and geeky grk wines. but i was blown away by this wine when i first tasted it paired with oysters freshly plucked from the adriatic sea in ston, croatia. the bačić family has preserved this local treasure, and for that they are heroes. more about this wine soon on the @winesofcroatia blog! #bačić #cetinka #baciccetinka #korcula #croatia #winesofcroatia #dalmatia #islandwine

text: one of the most inspirational stories we have ever heard posted on the blog today. brazilian model @julian.custodio worked in a sweatshop from the age of 8, was sent to model in china without speaking a word of english, was kidnapped by her agency to lose weight and despite working three jobs per day for a month, never received any of the money she earned. today she lives in europe and works as a successful model supporting her entire family, has set up two businesses and is looking forward to becoming a doctor. thank you for allowing us to tell your story to help countless others understand the dangers that modelling can involve and for showing the most important lessons in life are learned by living. 💫🙌🏽 link in bio

text:
before this relationship, i was outgoing, had many friends, hung out with my family regularly, my dog slept on my bed (sounds silly but i’ll make my point) and i was pretty darn happy. .
.
in the beginning of this relationship, i was still outgoing, i didn’t see my friends as often because my days always seemed to be full with all these new dates and plans, i talked to my family a lot, my dog slept on our bed and i was so freakin happy, i thought i was living a fairytale. .
.
a few months in and i was beginning to doubt myself and my judgement of who i hung out with, i started seeing all these flaws in my friends and family and didn’t trust everyone, my dog slept next to the bed and i was beginning to feel inexplicably depressed. .
.
fast forward. i’m quite the introvert. i live 14 hours from my friends and family. slowly i wasn’t receiving as many phone calls—i disappeared first, so then my friends started disappearing. i almost lost a sister who didn’t want to talk to me because she didn’t want to witness my continued deterioration. i gave my dog to my sister because i was tired of him sleeping in the closet and he was constantly hiding under the bed. my mood has consistently been sad, angry, resentful and depressed. .
.
you see, this didn’t happen overnight. and it was far from obvious. do you recognize this pattern? are you awake now? if you have kids and are sure the toxic parent would have the kids half the time (as in my case), would you let that person have the kids solo for that half of the time or would you stay so you could ensure their protection? does your life before this suddenly seem like a dream you wish you never woke up from? i know mine does.
name: Surviving a Narc & DV

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
domestic violence laws in california do not protect step parents! help make strangulation a felony!

this is a as good as they could do because the reality is i have been so freaking nice to these people for the majority of the time until the end when aurelia took it just too far. 
i have held her crying daughter in my arms for years now as she poured her heart out to me about her hurt feelings and i was there for her no matter how small the hurt was. i have helped her daughter be successful in school. i have cared for when she is sick. i have encouraged her to share all her feelings with her mother to resolve this. 
aurelia says to me just a week or so before she attacks me that i am brainwashing her daughter and it makes me happy to see her cry. i felt a f-bomb was appropriate especially if you attack me character after all these years i’ve put into helping make this better not worse. i would never inflict harm, neglect or ignore a child’s hurt feelings that is in my care which she was 50% or more of the time.

but her mom didn’t see her suffering and said she only acted this way to get attention. if she was so happy in her care why was she calling us crying to go pick her up and why was she begging us to live full time at our house? 
i brought my step daughter’s cat back. she and i drove over together. she refused to go up and see her mom because she was so hurt her mom wouldn’t temporarily let her have the cat while we worked through therapy even the therapist was dumbfounded. her deep throated moans and cries as we were forced to return her cat are etched in my memory.

text:
_
(함께 업로드한 사진 세장에 이어지는 글입니다.)
_
물론, 우리 중엔 가장 먼저 용기 내 노조 가입을 신청한 선배가 있었고ㅡ 그 선배가 어떤 이유에서인지 가입이 되지 않는다는 소식을 전해줬을 때.. 우리 모두 선택권이 없다는 사실을 알고는 아무 행동도 하지 못했으니 적어도 그 선배만큼은 ‘용기 없는 너가 문제’라는 비난조차도 받아서는 안 될 것이다. 
_
하지만, 이은지님 글을 보고 이 음성에 담지 못해 후회됐던 것은ㅡ 우리 아나운서들이 어떤 상황이었는지에 대한 해명이 아니다. 
_
기단법은 그 태생의 취지와는 달리, 악법이라는 것이 정설이다. 나는 사실 중노위에서 발언을 할 때, 법 자체보다는 그 진정한 취지를 보전하지 못한 사람들을 꼬집고 싶었다. 하지만, 결국 이 법을 적용’하는‘ 것은 노동자들의 생존여탈권을 쥔 자들. 이 법을 적용’받는’ 것은 생존권을 담보 맡겨야 할 노동자들인 것을 다시금 꼭꼭 씹어 보니, 결국 개선이 필요하다고 느껴지는 것은 사회 구성원이 아니라 법 규정 그 자체였다.
_
권력을 남용해 성적 자기결정권을 침해하는 것을 ‘그루밍 성범죄’라고 한다. 그렇다면, 일터에서 자유와 생각을 통제하고 하란 대로 안 하면 죽을 수도 있다는 무언의 강요를 하는 것도 인격적 자기결정권을 침해한 것 아닐까. 기단법을 두고 ‘그루밍의 제도화’라고 표현한 것에 소름이 돋은 이유다. 
_
권력형 성범죄 피해자에게 꽃뱀이네, 자기도 좋아서 했네ㅡ 하는 손가락질이 지금은 용납되지 않지만 불과 몇 년 전 #metoo 운동이 있기 전에는 당연시 나오던 말인것을 생각해보자. 지금 수많은 비정규직들이 기단법/파견법이라는 합법적 악법으로 인해 일하는동안에도 정당한 권리를 제한받을 뿐 아니라, 나갈때쯤엔 도리어ㅡ “계약직은 원래 2년 있다 나가는 걸 알고도 떼를 쓴다.”는 비난을 받는 것과 비슷하다. 
_
우리가 구제된 이유는 음성에서 밝힌 것처럼, 태생부터 부작용을 지니고 탄생한 이 기단법의 본래 취지가 선한 것이므로ㅡ 그 부작용을 최소화하고, 본래의 법 취지에 걸맞게 가려는 재판부 판단의 결과물ㅡ “갱신기대권, 전환기대권”이 있었기 때문이다. 이 권리들이 재판부에 의해 실체적 권리로 인정받지 못했다면, 기단법으로 인한 부작용은 지금에 비할 바 없이 심했을 것이라고 확신한다.
_
하지만 지금의 ‘조금 덜 나빠진 기단법 적용’을 위해서 수많은 기간제 노동자들이 대법원판결까지 기다리며 피눈물을 흘렸을 것을 생각하면 심장이 나가떨어질 것 같다. 그래서, 사법부의 보완 노력에도 불구하고 기단법이 악법이라는 것은 부정할 수 없다.
_
비단 기단법 뿐이랴ㅡ 우리 사회 대개의 부조리함이 실은 제도의 부재 또는 허술함으로 인한 것이고ㅡ 제도가 진보되기 위해 입법자들을 자극하는 것이 언론의 할 일인데.. 지금은 어떤 부당함의 중심에는 욕받이만 있고(물론 잘못한 사람은 욕도 먹어야 한다), 정작 다시금 그 상황을 유발할 수 있는 제도에 대한 논의는 이루어지지 않는 경우가 많은 것 같아 아쉽다. 
_
우리 사건 내용을 속속들이 아는 분들은, 2012년과 2017년 파업에 모두 참여하셨던 분들조차 우리를 최소한 적폐로는 보지 않는다. 하지만 모든 사람에게 그만치 자세한 사실관계를 전할 수 없는 한계가 있고, 그 귀책 사유는 대중의 것이 아니다. 그렇기 때문에 우리가 온당치 않은 오해와 비난을 받는다 하더라도 우리는 그저 묵묵히 욕을 들을 수밖에 없는 것이다. 
_
다만, 욕을 들을 때 듣더라도 욕만 듣고 끝나는 것은 안된다. 우리가 받은 비난과 욕 값으로, 방송계 비정규직 문제가 한걸음 진보되는 무언가 제도적 장치가 마련되기를 바라면 안 되는 것일까. 나아가, 기단법의 구멍이 메워지는 계기가 되기를 바라면 너무 큰 욕심일까. 
_
그래서 이번에도 부탁드린다. 우리 문제의 본질이 무엇인지 알고 있는 언론계 선배들ㅡ 또 입법 권한을 가지고 계신 분들, 그 밖에 팟캐스트/유튜브 스타 등 여러 인플루언서 분들께서 우리 같은 비극이 더 이상 반복되지 않도록 제도의 개선을 함께 고민해주시기를 말이다. 그리고 이번에도 약속드린다. 앞으로, 적어도 내가 적용받았던 이 기단법에 대해서만큼은 그 폐해를 알리는데 늘ㅡ 나름의 최선을 다하겠다는 것을.
_

name: 이선영
tweet_full:
_
(함께 업로드한 사진 세장에 이어지는 글입니다.)
_
물론, 우리 중엔 가장 먼저 용기 내 노조 가입을 신청한 선배가 있었고ㅡ 그 선배가 어떤 이유에서인지 가입이 되지 않는다는 소식을 전해줬을 때.. 우리 모두 선택권이 없다는 사실을 알고는 아무 행동도 하지 못했으니 적어도 그 선배만큼은 ‘용기 없는 너가 문제’라는 비난조차도 받아서는 안 될 것이다. 
_
하지만, 이은지님 글을 보고 이 음성에 담지 못해 후회됐던 것은ㅡ 우리 아나운서들이 어떤 상황이었는지에 대한 해명이 아니다. 
_
기단법은 그 태생의 취지와는 달리, 악법이라는 것이 정설이다. 나는 사실 중노위에서 발언을 할 때, 법 자체보다는 그 진정한 취지를 보전하지 못한 사람들을 꼬집고 싶었다. 하지만, 결국 이 법을 적용’하는‘ 것은 노동자들의 생존여탈권을 쥔 자들. 이 법을 적용’받는’ 것은 생존권을 담보 맡겨야 할 노동자들인 것을 다시금 꼭꼭 씹어 보니, 결국 개선이 필요하다고 느껴지는 것은 사회 구성원이 아니라 법 규정 그 자체였다.
_
권력을 남용해 성적 자기결정권을 침해하는 것을 ‘그루밍 성범죄’라고 한다. 그렇다면, 일터에서 자유와 생각을 통제하고 하란 대로 안 하면 죽을 수도 있다는 무언의 강요를 하는 것도 인격적 자기결정권을 침해한 것 아닐까. 기단법을 두고 ‘그루밍의 제도화’라고 표현한 것에 소름이 돋은 이유다. 
_
권력형 성범죄 피해자에게 꽃뱀이네, 자기도 좋아서 했네ㅡ 하는 손가락질이 지금은 용납되지 않지만 불과 몇 년 전 #metoo 운동이 있기 전에는 당연시 나오던 말인것을 생각해보자. 지금 수많은 비정규직들이 기단법/파견법이라는 합법적 악법으로 인해 일하는동안에도 정당한 권리를 제한받을 뿐 아니라, 나갈때쯤엔 도리어ㅡ “계약직은 원래 2년 있다 나가는 걸 알고도 떼를 쓴다.”는 비난을 받는 것과 비슷하다. 
_
우리가 구제된 이유는 음성에서 밝힌 것처럼, 태생부터 부작용을 지니고 탄생한 이 기단법의 본래 취지가 선한 것이므로ㅡ 그 부작용을 최소화하고, 본래의 법 취지에 걸맞게 가려는 재판부 판단의 결과물ㅡ “갱신기대권, 전환기대권”이 있었기 때문이다. 이 권리들이 재판부에 의해 실체적 권리로 인정받지 못했다면, 기단법으로 인한 부작용은 지금에 비할 바 없이 심했을 것이라고 확신한다.
_
하지만 지금의 ‘조금 덜 나빠진 기단법 적용’을 위해서 수많은 기간제 노동자들이 대법원판결까지 기다리며 피눈물을 흘렸을 것을 생각하면 심장이 나가떨어질 것 같다. 그래서, 사법부의 보완 노력에도 불구하고 기단법이 악법이라는 것은 부정할 수 없다.
_
비단 기단법 뿐이랴ㅡ 우리 사회 대개의 부조리함이 실은 제도의 부재 또는 허술함으로 인한 것이고ㅡ 제도가 진보되기 위해 입법자들을 자극하는 것이 언론의 할 일인데.. 지금은 어떤 부당함의 중심에는 욕받이만 있고(물론 잘못한 사람은 욕도 먹어야 한다), 정작 다시금 그 상황을 유발할 수 있는 제도에 대한 논의는 이루어지지 않는 경우가 많은 것 같아 아쉽다. 
_
우리 사건 내용을 속속들이 아는 분들은, 2012년과 2017년 파업에 모두 참여하셨던 분들조차 우리를 최소한 적폐로는 보지 않는다. 하지만 모든 사람에게 그만치 자세한 사실관계를 전할 수 없는 한계가 있고, 그 귀책 사유는 대중의 것이 아니다. 그렇기 때문에 우리가 온당치 않은 오해와 비난을 받는다 하더라도 우리는 그저 묵묵히 욕을 들을 수밖에 없는 것이다. 
_
다만, 욕을 들을 때 듣더라도 욕만 듣고 끝나는 것은 안된다. 우리가 받은 비난과 욕 값으로, 방송계 비정규직 문제가 한걸음 진보되는 무언가 제도적 장치가 마련되기를 바라면 안 되는 것일까. 나아가, 기단법의 구멍이 메워지는 계기가 되기를 바라면 너무 큰 욕심일까. 
_
그래서 이번에도 부탁드린다. 우리 문제의 본질이 무엇인지 알고 있는 언론계 선배들ㅡ 또 입법 권한을 가지고 계신 분들, 그 밖에 팟캐스트/유튜브 스타 등 여러 인플루언서 분들께서 우리 같은 비극이 더 이상 반복되지 않도록 제도의 개선을 함께 고민해주시기를 말이다. 그리고 이번에도 약속드린다. 앞으로, 적어도 내가 적용받았던 이 기단법에 대해서만큼은 그 폐해를 알리는데 늘ㅡ 나름의 최선을 다하겠다는 것을.
_

탄생한 이 기단법의 본래 취지가 선한 것이므로ㅡ 그 부작용을 최소화하고 , 본래의 법 취지에 걸맞게 가려는 재판부 판단의 결과물ㅡ “ 갱신기대권 , 전환기대권 ” 이 있었기 때문이다 . 이 권리들이 재판부에 의해 실체적 권리로 인정받지 못했다면 , 기단법으로 인한 부작용은 지금에 비할 바 없이 심했을 것이라고 확신한다 . _ 하지만 지금의 ‘ 조금 덜 나빠진 기단법 적용 ’ 을 위해서 수많은 기간제 노동자들이 대법원판결까지 기다리며 피눈물을 흘렸을 것을 생각하면 심장이 나가떨어질 것 같다 . 그래서 , 사법부의 보완 노력에도 불구하고 기단법이 악법이라는 것은 부정할 수 없다 . _ 비단 기단법 뿐이랴ㅡ 우리 사회 대개의 부조리함이 실은 제도의 부재 또는 허술함으로 인한 것이고ㅡ 제도가 진보되기 위해 입법자들을 자극하는 것이 언론의 할 일인데.. 지금은 어떤 부당함의 중심에는 욕받이만 있고 ( 물론 잘못한 사람은 욕도 먹어야 한다 ) , 정작 다시금 그 상황을 유발할 수 있는 제도에 대한 논의는 이루어지지 않는 경우가 많은 것 같아 아쉽다 . _ 우리 사건 내용을 속속들이 아는 분들은 , 2012년과 2017년 파업에 모두 참여하셨던 분들조차 우리를 최소한 적폐로는 보지 않는다 . 하지만 모든 사람에게 그만치 자세한 사실관계를 전할 수 없는 한계가 있고 , 그 귀책 사유는 대중의 것이 아니다 . 그렇기 때문에 우리가 온당치 않은 오해와 비난을 받는다 하더라도 우리는 그저 묵묵히 욕을 들을 수밖에 없는 것이다 . _ 다만 , 욕을 들을 때 듣더라도 욕만 듣고 끝나는 것은 안된다 . 우리가 받은 비난과 욕 값으로 , 방송계 비정규직 문제가 한걸음 진보되는 무언가 제도적 장치가 마련되기를 바라면 안 되는 것일까 . 나아가 , 기단법의 구멍이 메워지는 계기가 되기를 바라면 너무 큰 욕심일까 . _ 그래서 이번에도 부탁드린다 . 우리 문제의 본질이 무엇인지 알고 있는 언론계 선배들ㅡ 또 입법 권한을 가지고 계신 분들 , 그 밖에 팟캐스트/유튜브 스타 등 여러 인플루언서 분들께서 우리 같은 비극이 더 이상 반복되지 않도록 제도의 개선을 함께 고민해주시기를 말이다 . 그리고 이번에도 약속드린다 . 앞으로 , 적어도 내가 적용받았던 이 기단법에 대해서만큼은 그 폐해를 알리는데 늘ㅡ 나름의 최선을 다하겠다는 것을 . _ 루밍의제도화 단법 bc1617아나운서 👉🏻 youtube 검색 _ 이길어죄송합니다 니한두번도아니고 문제가 한걸음 진보되는 무언가 제도적 장치가 마련되기를 바라면 안 되는 것일까 . 나아가 , 기단법의 구멍이 메워지는 계기가 되기를 바라면 너무 큰 욕심일까 . _ 그래서 이번에도 부탁드린다 . 우리 문제의 본질이 무엇인지 알고 있는 언론계 선배들ㅡ 또 입법 권한을 가지고 계신 분들 , 그 밖에 팟캐스트/유튜브 스타 등 여러 인플루언서 분들께서 우리 같은 비극이 더 이상 반복되지 않도록 제도의 개선을 함께 고민해주시기를 말이다 . 그리고 이번에도 약속드린다 . 앞으로 , 적어도 내가 적용받았던 이 기단법에 대해서만큼은 그 폐해를 알리는데 늘ㅡ 나름의 최선을 다하겠다는 것을 . _ 루밍의제도화 단법 bc1617아나운서 👉🏻 youtube 검색 _ 이길어죄송합니다 니한두번도아니고 🌚 _ 감해주신모든분 text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
#lvi #lesvriaesinfos #lexpress «il est passé au travers de la vague #metoo. jusqu'à quand ? le réalisateur de bohemian rhapsody et usual suspects, bryan singer, fait face à de nouvelles accusations d'agressions sexuelles sur mineurs. une longue enquête publiée sur le site du mensuel américain the atlantic fait parler quatre hommes qui assurent avoir eu des relations qu'ils estimaient consenties avec le réalisateur alors qu'ils étaient mineurs, ou relatent des agressions. 
parmi ces témoignages, résume le huffington post, celui de v. valdovinos, qui a participé alors qu'il avait 13 ans au tournage d'un élève doué, sorti en 1998. il raconte à #theatlantic avoir été forcé, avec d'autres adolescents, à tourner nu une scène dans un vestiaire..»
le journal l'express faisaint de la rétention d'infos autant publié le huffington post..
#huffingtonpost #lvi #lesvraiesinfos
après le scoop sur harvey weinstein, tout le monde se disait que le suivant à tomber serait bryan singer." cela fait 25 ans qu'il réalise des films à hollywood, cela fait 25 ans que son nom est sujet à controverses.
ce mercredi 23 décembre, le média américainthe atlantic a publié une enquête choc, donnant la parole à plusieurs jeunes hommes, qui disent avoir été agressés sexuellement par l'un des réalisateurs américains les plus connus du moment: bryan singer. pendant un an, les journalistes #alexfrench et #maximillianpotter ont tenté de retrouver les victimes présumées de l'homme de désormais 53 ans..
et ils ont réussi à en faire parler quatre, dont un, #victorvaldovinos, a bien voulu témoigner sans le couvert de l'anonymat. tous avaient entre 13 et 18 ans au moment des faits dont ils font le récit: ils rapportent des relations consenties -avec des mineurs donc-, des orgies, mais aussi des viols et des agressions sexuelles..
(...)une première accusation était d'ailleurs sortie dans la presse, un homme du nom de #cesarsanchez-guzman accusant le réalisateur de l'avoir violé en 2003. quelques jours plus tard, un ancien compagnon de bryan singer avait lui livré un récit sans fard de la vie d'orgies et de drogues du cinéaste.» #bryansinger #xmen #metoo  #spiderman  #usualsuspects #industriesale #viols

text:
#rosannaarquette on backlash since speaking out against weinstein: ‘i don’t have an agent’...
“i think the people that have protected him all these years, that have known that he’s done this that have covered [it] up, who’ve paid off people to shut up, shut down stories that were coming out, threatened people — and they all know who they are — they’re complicit,” she said. “at some point they have to look at themselves in the mirror and say, ‘is this who i wanna be?’”
more than one year after telling her story to the new yorker about rejecting weinstein’s sexual advances in his hotel room, arquette is speaking out again — this time, on screen. she is the highest-profile woman to appear in the weinstein documentary, “untouchable,” which made its debut at the sundance film festival on friday evening.
“i don’t have an agent, so. i think there’s backlash for sure,” she said. “there’s a lot of people that made a lot of money from him, and continue to. there’s a boys club that protects the boys. he’s just one of many men, as we’re seeing more and more men being exposed for their awful behavior and their abuse of power.”
“i think hollywood keeps looking at their watches like, ‘when is this gonna end?’ and it’s not. it’s not going to end until people stop this bad behavior.”
“i’m sure if people thought they could make money with him and do something, the people that support him would do that. i think there are a lot of people that don’t want this to be true, and he desperately is trying to come back,” she said. “i heard he’s trying to work in europe, in france and italy, and who knows.”
“i think the man deserves to be in jail. many lives were shattered by his actions and his abuse of power. so i hope that there’s justice in that area.” she says she has not heard from weinstein whatsoever, since she spoke out against him. but she believes that she is being spied on by weinstein.
“i haven’t heard from him, but he’s made sure that me and other women have been spied on,” she said.

text:
| #metoo .
.
il y a longtemps qu’on ne s’est pas parlé. 19 années sont passé depuis notre dernière rencontre. on ne s’est jamais revus et je ne sais pas ce que tu es devenu. 
pourtant, tu existes encore en moi. involontairement. tu es une partie de qui je suis et je serai toujours une partie de toi. deux étrangers dont l’existence est liée par les liens du sang, deux étrangers pourtant de la même famille. il m’arrive de penser à toi, de me demander si tu regrettes ton geste ? .
.
tu sais, j’ai gaspillé beaucoup de mon temps à me demander « pourquoi moi »? j’ai réécrit l’histoire des milliers de fois, cherchant maladivement mes failles et tentant humainement de comprendre les tiennes. j’ai rêvé de me venger, fantasmé de ta souffrance et tyrannisé ton existence dans mes incalculables cauchemars. j’ai hurlé en silence et pleuré sans pouvoir faire couler mes larmes.
.
.
tu as volé mon enfance, détruit mes rêves . tu m’as brisée en plus de morceaux que je ne serai jamais capable d’assembler et marquée plus intensément encore que tout ce que j’aurais pu imaginer. .
.
je me suis sentie vide, complètement creuse et dépossédée.
j’ai peur du silence, je l’occupe constamment. je me méfie des gens et je n’ose plus marcher seule la nuit.
tu sais, je ne saurai jamais qui j’aurais pu être si ce n’était pas arrivé. tristement, mais heureusement, je suis devenue qui je suis. angoissée et méfiante, mais tellement courageuse et forte. .
.
je n’effacerai rien, ni ce que tu m’as fait subir ni ce que j’ai dû affronter pour m’en relever. je suis heureuse et fière de qui je suis devenue.
j’espère que le temps a fait son œuvre et que tu t’es pardonné comme moi je l’ai fait. j’espère que tu as avancé et trouvé la lumière quelque part en toi. je suis persuadée qu’elle existe.
.
.
tu sais, j’aimerais qu’on puisse se croiser dans une autre vie, ailleurs qu’ici. j’aimerais qu’on puisse se parler et peut-être enfin régler ce qui nous unit.
.
.
bonne chance .
.

text:
stop idolizing! they are not whom you think they truly are. and avoid trusting people too much, 
too quickly! majority of suspects’ victims are those who knew them, one way or another! stay safe! protect your loved ones. bad company corrupts good character. 
how to identify a pedophile
knowing the profile of a child molester
* 	understand that any adult could be a child molester.
* 	know that most child molesters are known to the children they abuse.
* 	know the common characteristics of a child molester.
* 	be aware of common behaviours demonstrated by child molesters.
* 	look for signs of grooming.

protecting your child from predators
* 	find out whether sex offenders live in your neighborhood.
* 	supervise your child's extracurricular activities.
* 	set up a nanny cam if you hire a babysitter.
* 	teach your child about staying safe online.
* 	make sure your child is feeling emotionally supported.
* 	teach your child to recognize inappropriate touching.
* 	recognize when something is out of sync with your child.

#여성민우회 #정기총회 에 왔습니다. 
오기 전 부터... 장소가 #서울여성플라자 로 된 걸 보고 기분이 묘했다. 
2년 전 이맘 때 이곳에서 #성폭력_가해자 #안희정 의 지지자모임이 있었고 그 때 나도 참석했으니까. 
와서 보니, 더 착잡하게도, 그때 지지자 모임이 열린 회의장 옆에 지금 #metoo 운동에 대한 전시가 있다. 인생이란 참~ 
사실 민우회 가입한 것도 안희정 사건의 충격 때문이기도 했으니. 심경 #복잡

text: these 15 lbs that were so “hard” to put on, were surprisingly much easier to take off! this 15 lbs represents years full of stress, heartache, anxiety, exhaustion, frustration,  and surrender. don’t be fooled—there were good parts, too—and i grew stronger in my mental health and healing, while my physical self suffered. it may not seem like a big milestone, but for me this is huge! the past 3-4 weeks have been a long time coming: i’m finally ready and willing to nurture another “part” of me; and i am just so excited that i’m back, and i’m ready to take on another 15. here we go! let’s get back to healthy habits and discipline. text:
first song i’ve written in a few years called “me too”
the point of this song is to  help illustrate the pain that is felt from a sexual assault/ physical abuse survivor to someone who does not have much knowledge or experience on the subject. 
i think there is a barrier/ disconnect between the understanding and personalization of this issue and that it’s  not just another statistic or an issue on the news. there is, i guarantee , at least once person among you who has endured this trauma. if not you, or someone you’re already are of that is close to you, you interact daily with someone who has endured this trauma whether it be a coworker or acquaintance. sexual assault is so common among us and for those who have no experience with it, but free remain blind to the frequency of this happening as well as the affect it has on survivors. 
what i hope to achieve with this song is to illustrate the pain that i, among many other survivors have lived through. to personalize the issue for those who have not been affected by this yet so they have an understanding and  we can start talking.
i understand the instrumentals are not on a precessional level nor is the sound quality, but that’s not really why this song is being posted. the meaning is in the message. 
so, #metoo
name: 𝙲𝚕𝚊𝚒𝚛𝚎

text:
it may be surprising to some, but often times, i feel the most sexy, wearing something like i am right now.
-
to the outside world i am a in warm and comfy clothing. to me, this picture speaks self confidence. in boatloads. i say that as humbly as possible. 🙏🏽 -
1. i made it through the holidays w/o gaining weight and actually started 2019 the lightest i’ve been in over a year or three - it’s been such a yo-yo that i kinda forgot. 🤷🏽‍♀️ but i know i’m lighter. 
2. i see that little belly roll and i’m totally ok w/her. i finally learned that i needed to love my body, in order for my body to love me back. w/that mutual love, she (this body) and i are letting go of the weight that was metaphorical & literal baggage, in every sense of them.
3. i’m sexy,... my way. firstly by knowing the wildfire that’s burning in me and propelling me into the greatest season of my life yet. secondly, by wearing some sexy ass lace underwear beneath these warm leggings that are intended for no one else but me.  if they end up being for someone else then that’s a bonus, not the goal. ¿me están oyendo?! 4. i’m finally embracing three parts of myself that i’ve struggled w/ the most: - being extremely sensitive, emotional, etc - having an innate dirty mind and sex appeal that’s a struggle b/c i’m also a childhood sexual abuse survivor so sexual anything carries a lot of shame and guilt for me - it’s ok to forgive myself for choosing a path in life that i thought meant i’d ruined my life for good. now i see they were necessary bricks i had to re-lay in order to stand where i do. i feel more “cemented”. like bricks. 🧱 -
5.  all of the above are still somewhat ‘silent’ inside of me. i only let a bit of that boil to the surface. usually. now i’m feeling empowered and prepared, and it’s displayed by my choice in clothing w/o asking where we’re going b/c i would obsess over being correctly dressed. now i frankly don’t give a fuck. pardon my french. but not really. 💋 -
that to me 👆🏽is so.much of what makes me feel sexy. it’s a mosaic of layers and feelings & emotions that make us have a spark and sexy is another word for it. ¡chispa! / a / #curlycurvypassion

text:
life 
has been a firing line
a stoning
from which i have emerged
intact, perhaps
but standing, surely
as in “i am here”
and you cannot look beyond that
though they will
i may not be standing surely
as in “steadfast”
but you wait

i will reach the peaks
of the mountains i was meant to climb
before the avalanches buried me 
alive
alive 
alive
pulling at pockets of air 
i picked my way out
bracing against the shifting earth 
collecting scars and badges of 
suffering no one saw
me 
no one saw

i can measure this path 
without their company 
without their criticism
this mountain is mine to conquer
they won’t be the saviors
i am the hero
of my own story #ptsd #metoo #depression #trauma #anxiety #resilience #healing

text:
4 простых шага!
для эффективного и правильного похудения необходим комплексный подход. программа energy slim задействует все основные механизмы снижения веса и активизирует различные системы организма в нужной последовательности.
шаг 1
drain effect дренирующий напиток
выводит лишнюю жидкость
устраняет отеки
уменьшает объемы
дает старт процессу эффективного похудения
шаг 2
foodcontrol натуральный продукт для контроля аппетита
помогает легко контролировать аппетит
формирует правильные пищевые привычки
позволяет сократить размер порции на 30-50%
шаг 3
metabolic активатор обмена веществ
стимулирует обменные процессы и жиросжигание
лишние килограммы уходят
способствует переработке жировых запасов в энергию
шаг 4
body shape продукт для подтяжки фигуры
способствует подтяжке силуэта: поддерживает упругость мышц и кожи
препятствует образованию новых жировых отложений
помогает закрепить достигнутые результаты
для кого?
для тех, кто хочет худеть легко.
для тех, кто хочет контролировать свой аппетит.
для тех, кто хочет избавиться от отеков.
для тех, кто хочет ускорить метаболизм.
для тех, кому важен гарантированный результат.

text:
yo yesterday and today were (are)  pretty emotional days for me...
⠀⠀
yesterday i got super hungry because when i workout hard i go through nutrient like water. ⠀⠀
naturally, i didn’t realize i was hungry and i started feeling sad 😢 is not a sensation that my body recognizes. ⠀⠀
the funny thing is that underlining sadness was brought to the surface and felt due to my lack of energy. i was unable to maintain a positive attitude, and the wave of limiting believes sites opportunity and came rushing in.
⠀⠀
honestly, that’s a good thing! why is that a good thing? well because i had to face something that i was masking with an excellent healthy habit lol 😂 crazy how even healthy things can become bad habits!
⠀⠀
and honestly, i think this was bound to happen because the affirmations i’m doing are demanding me to align myself with my greatest desires. ⠀⠀
so it seems as i’m aligning, things are coming up for me. you can’t wash the dishes without getting your hands dirty! ((if someone says you some gloves i’m going to find you and punch you)) 😝 ⠀⠀
this is my fourth week consistently playing my affirmations. i’ve been on an absolute highest! super productive! super on top of everything that i need to be doing! just perfect 👌🏽 ⠀⠀
in the last two days talk about crash & burn! smh 🤦🏽‍♂️

text:
strength...what defines strength?.
strength is the girl in your class who gets picked on every single day by her peers, but continues to show up to class & thrive. strength is the lady you pass by at the mall who looks completely happy with life, & she is...she’s grateful for the life & time she does have, but she’s also fighting for her life...fighting the awful disease of breast cancer. strength is the parent who has lost their child too soon/too young, but decides to have faith & keep on going. strength is your aunt... she’s always smiling & helping others, she puts herself before anyone, she the most lovable person you know. but what you don’t see is the husband with the drinking problem who tends to get verbally & physically abusive with threats thrown at your aunt. strength is your best friend who deals with anxiety/depression/ptsd. it’s a battle they fight every day/every night. not a lot of education is out there & they don’t have family members who have had to deal with any form of mental illness. they feel alone at times, & have been asked about the “crazy pills” they need to take. and yet they still peel themselves out of bed every morning & live a “normal” life...at least from what you can see. that’s why it’s known as an “invisible illness”.
strength is coming to terms with being sexually abused as a child, the memories start flooding back which trigger panic attacks. it’s reaching out for help whether with a therapist/counselor or a support group. kick that shame & guilt out the window because it’s not your fault! start journaling or talking about it with someone with whom you can trust. shame hides in silence, so try and let it out. learn what the best healing process is for you. there is no right or wrong answer. what’s that saying?... the strongest people are not those who show strength in front of us, but those who win battles we know nothing about. never assume that loud is strong & quiet is weak. #strength #whatisstrength #keepgoing #noshame #havefaith #cancersucks #verbalabuseisstillabuse #physicalabuseawareness #iam1in5 #metoo #timesup #stillwerise #survivor #neverassume #reachout #trauma #youarestrong #crazypills #mentalhealthawareness
name: shiningthroughthestorm
tweet_full:
strength...what defines strength?.
strength is the girl in your class who gets picked on every single day by her peers, but continues to show up to class & thrive. strength is the lady you pass by at the mall who looks completely happy with life, & she is...she’s grateful for the life & time she does have, but she’s also fighting for her life...fighting the awful disease of breast cancer. strength is the parent who has lost their child too soon/too young, but decides to have faith & keep on going. strength is your aunt... she’s always smiling & helping others, she puts herself before anyone, she the most lovable person you know. but what you don’t see is the husband with the drinking problem who tends to get verbally & physically abusive with threats thrown at your aunt. strength is your best friend who deals with anxiety/depression/ptsd. it’s a battle they fight every day/every night. not a lot of education is out there & they don’t have family members who have had to deal with any form of mental illness. they feel alone at times, & have been asked about the “crazy pills” they need to take. and yet they still peel themselves out of bed every morning & live a “normal” life...at least from what you can see. that’s why it’s known as an “invisible illness”.
strength is coming to terms with being sexually abused as a child, the memories start flooding back which trigger panic attacks. it’s reaching out for help whether with a therapist/counselor or a support group. kick that shame & guilt out the window because it’s not your fault! start journaling or talking about it with someone with whom you can trust. shame hides in silence, so try and let it out. learn what the best healing process is for you. there is no right or wrong answer. what’s that saying?... the strongest people are not those who show strength in front of us, but those who win battles we know nothing about. never assume that loud is strong & quiet is weak. #strength #whatisstrength #keepgoing #noshame #havefaith #cancersucks #verbalabuseisstillabuse #physicalabuseawareness #iam1in5 #metoo #timesup #stillwerise #survivor #neverassume #reachout #trauma #youarestrong #crazypills #mentalhealthawareness

text:
i've cried so many tears throughout the last few years, its unbelievable. i've felt my tears rise up in my throat, and i feel like i'm choking i'm so scared. scared of loving again, dreaming again and redefining my life.

but i chose to wipe away the countless tears and confront my fears...not just once but over and over again. as a result my faith and peace have grown. even though my year has been crappy so far, i've been able to have more peace and faith then i thought i had in me. peace that tells me everything will work out for my good, and faith that god will carry me through.

resilient af.

still a queen 👑✊.
.
.
.

text:
i cannot believe #periodcon is tomorrow… signed a few hundred of these for all of you coming! we will be gathering #menstrualmovement activists from around the world together for this two-day event along with an incredible roster of speakers right here in nyc! 🙈
.
period activism is challenging because we’re fighting stigma that is so embedded into society and culture — we’re pushing against the status quo around a topic that most people don’t want to talk about or even mention. it’s hard not to feel discouraged by the giggles, smirks, and rejections we might experience regularly from just standing up for something we are truly passionate about: menstrual equity. that’s why #periodcon is so special, it’s an opportunity where everyone is smiling and cheering and hugging, all excited and hungry to talk more about periods, menstruation, period poverty, and so much more… it’s amazing… ❤️
.
anyways, to all the chapter members coming: you inspire me. in the rough patches of this event planning process, i just kept remembering who i was doing this for, and that filled me with all the motivation i needed. i hope that this weekend you have so much fun, learn lots, and leave feeling inspired and ready to take action. 2019 is going to be big, let’s do this. 👊🏽
.
huge thank you to @sharonamckee for bringing this event to life behind the scenes, @betsy_na and vincent for being my partners in @periodmovement , @darawilk for working with me to pull in sponsors, and @tuprimaeira for engaging our beautiful chapter network ❤️
.
pc @chloe.belangia

text:
⚠️this may be upsetting⚠️ ———————————————
many people know that i use art to express myself and deal with the things that go on in my life. this poem is something i just wrote, but have been putting over a year of thought into. finally writing it was a relief and sharing it is hard, but i’ve seen others who have experienced similar events do it with wonderful results. i consider poetry one of the most beautiful forms of art and an amazing way to let people know that someone somewhere knows how you feel to some degree. ———————————————
560 days ago
i agreed to be yours.
i beamed as i gave you my word
which you swore meant so much to you.
each day you took my hand in yours
with a care 
i had never received,
a deliberation that i had never seen.
and what seemed to be
a love far too good to be true.
as the days passed
your hand no longer
laid intertwined with mine
but across my face
that you had sworn
was the light of your life.
i told you i wanted you to be happy, not upset
but my words seemed to ricochet
off of your empty chest. 
510 days ago
things seemed better.
you came to see me
but that too proved grim.
because 510 days ago
you took my words
and the hands you once held
and crushed them on the floor
with a deliberation i had never seen.
and i cried
as you took me for yourself
and swore it meant so much to you.
and you took the sweet vanilla scent
i used to wear before you used it to set your sights on me, and before you
instilled the fear that someone else
just like you would do the same.
and you took away the beauty 
of solitary walks 
beneath the night sky. 
and you took my ability to trust
and somehow,
despite your exile,
211 days ago
you took away the one true love i had 
and made me crush him
while i swore he still meant so much to me.
and 510 days later,
it still crushes
me too. ~samantha mckinnon
———————————————

text:
#cine #opinion el óscar y la enfermedad de lo políticamente correcto. parte 3. 
siento que este año se les ha ido la mano, pero esta atracción por lo políticamente correcto no es novedad.

hace unos años, la muy elemental y predecible (aunque bien filmada) cinta de barry jenkins moonlight (2016) fue nominada resultando ganadora como mejor película.

desde su nominación supe que ganaría y también que el premio era inmerecido. no porque la película este mal filmada o no merezca algún reconocimiento. más bien porque había otras que quizás lo merecían más. si ganó fue debido a su temática y a la necesidad de la academia de quedar bien (una vez más) con el colectivo lgbt.

incluir entre las ganadoras una película sobre la homosexualidad funcionó en su campaña por parecer “inclusivos” y “justos” en su forma de repartir sus galardones.

de igual modo, la manía por lo políticamente correcto también estuvo presente el año pasado cuando fue nominada greta gerwig en la categoría de mejor director. su película lady bird (2018) no es precisamente una demostración de creatividad o innovación a la hora de hacer cine. su nominación fue una evidente necesidad de quedar bien con las mujeres en medio del revuelo que armó (y sigue armando) el #metoo.

la enfermedad de lo políticamente correcto permite obviar un premisa elemental cuando se trata del arte: la obra (y quien la ejecuta) debería defenderse sola. nada hay fuera de ella (ninguna razón social, de raza o género) que pueda estar por encima de la obra misma.

siendo mujer, latina y negra entiendo que es necesario potenciar la inclusión en el mundo. nadie debe ser discriminado por su raza, sexo u condición. no obstante, nadie merece ser premiado por ninguna de esas razones.

así las cosas, este será un año más en que no veré el óscar. .
.
.
.
.

en los posts anteriores las otras partes. leela completa en 👉 https://www.desdelaplaza.com/author/lugueto/ .
.

text:
today, i woke up to this surprise in my mailbox. i feel so blessed to have a friend @shehreen3 who cares about every aspect of my life. the most being, my mental health. @zudo.co is a nonprofit organization which caters to serve women coming out sexual abusive relationships or domestic violent homes. they work closely with craftsmen to design arabic, south asian, and islamic influenced accessories while simultaneously encouraging these communities to break the silence about taboo topics, including domestic violence, sexual assault, and mental health. i know for some of us instagram is a virtual reality to show the perfection of our lives. however, let’s keep it raw. nothing, really is perfect. and maybe, that’s what makes it real. 
#zudo #stereotypes #breakthesilence #metoo #healing

let's start at the beginning of all beginnings: vaginal health.
despite the fact that all women have one and literally every person came from one, 50% of young women cannot properly label a vagina on a medical diagram. there is an urgent need to change this— or at the very least, to have a conversation. a healthy vagina is incredibly important to your physical, mental and emotional health, and of course your sexual function. and you deserve to feel great in every way.
your pleasure principal is here to help. let's change the way we think, speak and feel about our vaginas, starting now. send dm if interested in learning more.

text: “ tienes que ser comprensiva con los hombres”. eso decía el psicólogo al que fui siendo aún menor. era habitual ir por montera, callao, preciados, y escuchar palabras groseras. la hora de la siesta es la peor. de noche hay mucha gente pero después de comer no tanta. una vez se me acercó un mendigo a pedir algo y fui amable. me quiso dar un abrazo y le dejé y me metió mano. un compañero le dijo “eh, comparte”. dije que me tenía que ir y él me dijo su nombre. le volví a ver muchas veces pero nunca le saludé. ni siquiera sé si se lo conté a aquel psicólogo tan sórdido. no es un #metoo. esto es otra cosa. es un dibujo de algo que a veces pasaba.  a veces se te acercaban los viejos, los pobres, los crónicos, los contrahechos. no podías ser tan mala persona de rechazarles con virulencia. se nos pedía vivir en jaque mate, o eso fue lo que entendimos.

text:
✨hi again!✨⠀
⠀
after making my initial post introducing my account, i wanted to make a separate post introducing me 😊⠀
⠀
even though i am choosing to remain anonymous — cloaked by the bit of security from my own art and choosing not to share identifying information, i still want to those who stumble upon my page to know me better.⠀
⠀
i’m a cis-het woman, in my mid-20s, located in the us. i have my bachelors, which i received from my dream university (still shocked, even nearly a decade later). i adore animals. some of my favorite things in life are dancing and music, so i can often be found budgeting for the next music festival that has caught my eye. i love science and i spend way too much time lusting over makeup. i’m a huge book worm. i love to trash talk while watching sports. someday i hope to pursue my phd.⠀
⠀
fairly normal 😉⠀
⠀
but, that’s not why i created @my.reclamation⠀
⠀
i’ve been raped, twice. (i’ll cover this more in-depth in future posts)⠀
⠀
the first time was july 10th, 2008. he was my boyfriend at the time. it was my first experience with sex and tainted it for me for years. i internalized it so deeply and for so long i made myself physically ill. i was harassed about it in my small-town high school. my self-confidence was zapped and my body made me feel sick and dirty.⠀
⠀
the second time i was raped was some time in august 2015. i was on a second date. the first date was fine, normal. no red flags. i was sipping on a cocktail, my first, when he urged me to take a shot with a guy sitting a few seats down at the bar. after returning to my drink i don’t remember leaving the bar. i woke up to being assaulted, forced to do drugs, bruised, and in ripped clothing with a shoe missing.⠀
⠀
i almost lost my life while recovering from my second rape. it’s why i say “#rapesurvivor” instead of “#rapevictim.”⠀
⠀
but now, i’m here. i’m getting individual and group therapy. i’m seeing a psychiatrist and being compliant with my meds. i’m trying to re-establish a workout routine to feel on top and in charge of my body. i live in near-constant fear of slipping away and losing functionality again... but now, i’m here. #metoo #speakup #endthesilence #mentalhealth

text:
________________________________________у каждого из нас свой ад внутри
и называется он "память".
там беснуется все, что мы творим.
и не стереть это, не исправить.

предательства, страхи, пережитые обиды
сжигают душу нам дотла.
неудивительно, что равнодушия темный идол
там получает абсолютные права.

text:
not everyday is rainbows and unicorn toots. ⁣
🦄💨🌈⁣
⁣
and if you are ever looking at someone’s social media feed and comparing your life to them, cut that ish out!! ⁣
⁣
social media is the highlight reel...even my vulnerable, real and raw posts are usually thoroughly written out, read twice and edited along with me adding a pretty filter too. (just like this one) ⁣
⁣
today was filled with constipation screams, acidic poops and getting hit in the face with a flailing toddler arm...twice. ⁣
⁣
and lots of oils and a few mommy tears. ⁣
⁣
it was a super stinky and super gross day, y’all, but i always find the silver lining. ⁣
⁣
silver lining: it tested me and all of the soul work i’ve been doing and i feel so good about how i handled the chaos today. ⁣
i also became extra grateful for our exceptional health we have daily. ⁣
this is so rare and that makes me happy. ⁣
⁣
so back to the point...social media is smoke and mirrors. we all deal with crap. ⁣
*pun intended ⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣
.⁣⁣

#lesscontrolmoreflow #awakening⁣

text:
#cine #opinion el óscar y la enfermedad de lo políticamente correcto. parte 3. 
siento que este año se les ha ido la mano, pero esta atracción por lo políticamente correcto no es novedad.

hace unos años, la muy elemental y predecible (aunque bien filmada) cinta de barry jenkins moonlight (2016) fue nominada resultando ganadora como mejor película.

desde su nominación supe que ganaría y también que el premio era inmerecido. no porque la película este mal filmada o no merezca algún reconocimiento. más bien porque había otras que quizás lo merecían más. si ganó fue debido a su temática y a la necesidad de la academia de quedar bien (una vez más) con el colectivo lgbt.

incluir entre las ganadoras una película sobre la homosexualidad funcionó en su campaña por parecer “inclusivos” y “justos” en su forma de repartir sus galardones.

de igual modo, la manía por lo políticamente correcto también estuvo presente el año pasado cuando fue nominada greta gerwig en la categoría de mejor director. su película lady bird (2018) no es precisamente una demostración de creatividad o innovación a la hora de hacer cine. su nominación fue una evidente necesidad de quedar bien con las mujeres en medio del revuelo que armó (y sigue armando) el #metoo.

la enfermedad de lo políticamente correcto permite obviar un premisa elemental cuando se trata del arte: la obra (y quien la ejecuta) debería defenderse sola. nada hay fuera de ella (ninguna razón social, de raza o género) que pueda estar por encima de la obra misma.

siendo mujer, latina y negra entiendo que es necesario potenciar la inclusión en el mundo. nadie debe ser discriminado por su raza, sexo u condición. no obstante, nadie merece ser premiado por ninguna de esas razones.

así las cosas, este será un año más en que no veré el óscar. .
.
.
.
.

en los posts anteriores las otras partes. leela completa en 👉 https://www.desdelaplaza.com/author/lugueto/ .
.

text:
something you should never ever apologize for is protecting your mental health. i definitely suggest doing everything you can to get the relationship to a healthy place. if that work isn’t mutual and doesn’t protect your mental health, leave.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
a few years ago, i had to write off two important people in my life because they were simply too toxic to keep around. since then, i have been so much more happy and able to grow and prosper after getting rid of that extra weight holding me back.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
i still have people contacting me criticizing my decision to remove them from my life. i just have to ignore that and focus on the joy i have in my life. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
what i am really getting at is that you are never required to keep someone close that is so toxic in your life that your mental state. i truly believe that working it out the best you can first then remove them if every effort for restoration has been exhausted and it is still a toxic relationship. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
your mental state is always worth protecting.
⁣⁣
👚: sita top by @elegantees ⁣⁣
🥿: @therootcollective ⁣⁣
👂🏽💍: @designedforjoy ⁣
⁣⁣
disclaimer: i am not saying if you are being abused to stay for any reason. i suggest reaching out to a local nonprofit or calling 9-11 to leave quickly. 😘

text:
morning rituals are something i've always thought about but never committed to because i don't like the idea of heavily relying on routine (something i am very prone to do). so lately i've been practising a loose series of morning rituals that can be sort of adapted for each day no matter where i am physically or mentally. 
each morning i try to get up as i wake up and have a glass of cold water to kick-start. then i find whichever space that calls to me to write down a "to-do" list of achievable things that help ground & set the intention for the day. there's no real time limit on these steps because mornings to me are a s-l-o-w process. when i've set my intentions, i stretch in the sun & warm down outside with a big glass of icy water - today it's an iced lemon debloat tea - and a pukapuka.

it's pretty bloody great, and i recommend anyone who suffers facing the world in the morning to try it ✨

text:
anger. 😡 "there are so many people in the world that should be more angry. 
it’s a sign. 
when we’re not in tune with that, we lose our humanity.

we lose our opportunity for change. 
we lose our opportunity for connection with other people that are also angry about the same thing.

it’s a shame and we can’t afford it, we cannot afford for people to be void of their emotions.” -arj

as my next guest said so eloquently during our recent conversation... for me, for so long, anger has been this thing that's to be avoided at all costs. 
don't go there. 🛑
we've got to somehow side-step around this very real, natural human emotion. 
it had always been framed for me as a really bad thing because when expressed it undoubtedly wreaked havoc & brought about frightening chaos. 
and as i've been growing in awareness around this, i've learned that anger is quite possibly the most extraordinary emotion to inspire meaningful change.

on one hand, anger can cause harm when used from a wounded state, spewing painful, shrapnel at all those around. 
but to the contrary, anger can evoke tidal waves of good & just change when used mindfully.

when you feel anger, it is a sign... a loud indication that something isn't sitting right. and when you are able to harness that anger for good, great change can happen. 
what's even more remarkable, is when groups, communities, bodies of people come together & channel their shared anger for change, liberation, freedom, liberty, justice, peace.

global movements happen. 
#metoo
#lovewins
#blacklivesmatter
#bornthisway
#equality
#humanrights
#womensmarch

meet, @andrearanaej , a courageous soul, leading the way and changing the conversation on anger, activism, impact & how we can cultivate a world that is increasingly more just & free. 
andréa ranae believes that together, we rise. she is deeply committed to doing her part in cultivating a world that works for everyone & does so by placing her work at the intersections of personal growth, social justice & conscious business.

listen now ➡️ www.thejenmavrosshow.com itunes, spotify, iheartradio, google play, stitcher.

text:
it’s over! the shutdown is over. for now... all that. for what? he achieved nothing! except needlessly and callously punishing the public — and — showing us all who’s really in charge in #washingtondc.
thank you #nancypelosi for standing up against our wannabe-bully-in-chief and keeping the focus where it should be: on the 800,000+ federal workers who have been missing multiple paychecks [including some legally required to still work] and countless other americans who are feeling the residual effects of this painful and dumb #trumpshutdown. out of touch and just plain cruel. but, why exactly was our government shutdown over american taxpayers paying for the wall — when #mexico is supposed to be paying for the wall? i don't give a crap about his fan’s spins and interpretations of what he meant to say, or what he really means… he said: "i will build a great wall -- and nobody builds walls better than me, believe me --and i'll build them very inexpensively. i will build a great, great wall on our southern border, and i will make mexico pay for that wall. mark my words." words…marked. he was very clear and specific. he even put it in writing! he wants money for his stupid wall?…it's going to have to be in pesos. end of discussion. #democrats now control of the house and will put forth sensible legislation to benefit the people of this country. and, for the first time, will conduct real congressional oversight of #trump…his life will now [and deservedly so] become a virtual and perpetual deep colonoscopy…the saudis. abuse of power. corruption. ethics. kavanaugh. tax returns. obstruction of justice. #russia….you name it…we'll really start getting to the bottom of it…all! to save #america we must hold to account the inept, corrupt and amoral unindicted co-conspirator in the oval office: #illegitimate #failingpresident #donaldtrump. #lovetrumpshate #nevertrump #msnbc #foxnews #cnn #journalism #moveon #trumpprotest #notmypresident #politics #journalism #indivisible #makeamericagreatagain #womensmarch #crazytown #metoo #bluewave #maga

text:
i’m exhausted for all the women i used to be.
my mug is empty but the coffee can’t cut through the fog.
.
i’m exhausted for my 16 year old self, the moment of confusion when a friends father told me “no grown man could say no to that.”
.
i am so tired today, the cumulative bags under my eyes from years of this shit weighing my head down.
.
i’m exhausted for my 20 year old self, in that dorm room, on that night. the clothes on the floor implicated me, and it was like he had cotton in his ears. a yes is a yes until it’s a no, especially when she’s screaming it--just a friendly psa from your local feminist.
.
i can feel the weight of that night in my bones, the weight i carried for the better part of a decade. a time when i sought solace in bulimia and was searching for part of myself in the bottom of a double tall.
.
i am exhausted for all the women i used to be. all the weight laid across young shoulders. innuendos, unwanted touch, toxic caretaking, leering eyes, being cat called at 13 years old, marketing and movies that taught me my body is a sexualized object, made for what it can do for a man.
.
not what it can do for me.
.
if i had a gray hair for every time a man bulldozed my boundaries, forced me to be a bitch because i’m as good as mute if i’m being nice about turning him down the first two times, or took my platonic friendship or professional relationship for a green light, i’d have...oh wait.
.
this is a trigger warning, as in, i’m easily triggered by men taking without asking, by unsolicited assumptions, by the cotton in your ears. hear me the first time or kindly fuck off.
.
today, i’m exhausted for all the women i used to be.

text:
living with ptsd is real. for those who know someone with the symptoms or has ptsd, understand you cannot "fix" them (if you're unsure of what to look for , please google ptsd, do as much research as you can).
understand they are not necessarily broken (although we often feel that way) but things like, "it's in the past now" or "you're not there anymore".... "you're home now".... "think of something else" are not generally things that are ok to say. instead, you could ask what the person wants you to do incase something comes up (trigger, flashback, nightmare, outburts, low times, anniversaries etc.) sometimes we'll be able to let you know... other times we don't know ourselves, but for you just to comfort us without saying a word. .
ptsd is not just for military or ex-military personnel. anyone who has had a traumatic experience anytime on their life can have some sort of ptsd. please keep that in mind and be kind to others, they might be battling a war you know nothing about.. ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
#ptsd #survivor #metoo #men #women #teen #victim #war #military #trauma #recovery #strong #mentalhealth #anniversary #depression #selfdestructive  #nightmare #dreams #haunted #alone #pills #myjourney

text:
complex trauma is ongoing or repeated interpersonal trauma (abuse), within a captivity situation, where the victim perceives no viable means to escape.

most ongoing child abuse, is complex trauma. the child is vulnerable, at the mercy of the caregivers and unable to escape. other examples where complex trauma can occur are sex trafficking, prisoner of war, severe domestic violence.

complex post traumatic stress disorder, can result from enduring complex trauma.

complex ptsd has specific symptoms, that are not listed within the diagnostic criterion for (uncomplicated) post traumatic stress disorder.

these specific symptoms, are deep and pervasive issues with trust, abandonment, emotion regulation, isolation and many more.

one of the most common symptoms, and the hardest to understand and recognize, are emotional flashbacks. these are where emotions from the past, are triggered by something occurring now. these emotional flashbacks, do not have a visual aspect to them like flashbacks many ptsd sufferers experience. when there is something visual, it is far easier to understand – this is a flashback.
https://youwillbearwitness.com/2019/01/25/emotional-flashbacks-and-complex-trauma/ #youwillbearwitness #emdr #erinfado #metoo #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #trauma #therapydog #doitfordolly #dissociativeidentitydisorder

text:
this is me! confident in my own skin!
i’ve chosen brave this year as my focus. regardless of what others may think. imagine if we pushed aside insecurities and our concern about what others think.... fortune favors the brave....and the curious.
•
so...i remember when no one had ever heard of younique...and then it was "oh, the company with that eyelash stuff, right?" and now we are a global billion dollar cosmetic and skin care company in 13 countries. (yes not just the usa!)
•
well, we are about to release something that in a few years, people are going to be saying "can you imagine being there when they first released that?"
•
i would love to tell you more. but i’m not going to beg you. i wasn’t begged. i joined. then quit. someone continued to share. she waited for me. i watched. others continued when i found every excuse:

i’ve failed at other things, i’ll fail at this
scared
tired
busy
too busy
training for an ironman
not interested
insecure
fearful
skeptical
dont know how to do makeup
don’t wear makeup
dont have enough followers
hate taking selfies
don’t do ‘lives’
i’m not pretty enough
don’t wanna spend $99
that’s not for me
what will people think
•
this is up to you right now.  what have you got to lose?
i’m already leading 4 others this month, made my investment back and it’s amazing!!!
•
🙋🏻‍♀️ dm me or comment let’s chat!

text:
are you a feminist and still consume dairy?
read below!
just like humans, cows have to be pregnant in order to produce milk. they’re forcibly impregnated on a device called a “rape rack”.
.
once the calf is born- if it’s a male, he’s sent to slaughter within days of birth.
if it’s a female, she’s separated from her mother immediately and raised in tiny outdoor pens. denied the milk from their mother.
.
mother cows are known to cry out for their babies for days. imagine having your child taken away to either be killed or a prisoner.
.
if you’re a feminist, and consuming dairy. please watch “dairy is scary” on youtube. you cannot call yourself a feminist and not be vegan.
.
this flashback friday is dedicated to when we disrupted the woman’s march in miami with a vegan message.
:
go vegan. 💚

text:
el maltrato diario de ciert@s alumnos así me deja al final de la semana. poco me parecen 2 días para recuperarme. 
la curiosidad mató al 😿(aunque murió más sabio 😼) no me sigas por algo malo, que el/la que siembra recoge 🔮💣💥👑🍀 tampoco lo hagas si eres menor.
👶👦👲👧🚼 si pinchas en este enlace y tiras hacia abajo un poquito, verás cómo me presenta la editorial mito: https://mitoeditorial.blogspot.com/p/autor-invitado.html 👋😹👍🐩💫
puedes leer artículos míos en diario alhaurín y en 101 málaga, así como en las revistas culturales guatiní (miami) y mimeógrafo (méxico). también me presentaron en la ventana del arte (la guía más completa sobre exposiciones en españa), revista one stop y en webs y blogs como: munduky y repoelas (ambas españolas) y, en inglés, en art reveal magazine https://go.shr.lc/2u3tk4e 🍹🎻🎶🦄💰💂 📚mis novelas llegan a cualquier lugar 🗺 desde: 
my novels arrive everywhere from

http://www.bubok.es/autores/bokusu

pincha el enlace en mi perfil.
verás que están en papel; que puedes leer las primeras páginas, algunas críticas y más... la 1ª también en formato digital. son para mayores de 18 años.🔞 you can click the link in my profile. you'll see they are in paper, you can read the first pages, some critics and more... the first one is also for ebook, your computer, etc. they are for adults. ✌😘👍 todo lo ocurrido desde que decidí publicar y más en: http://www.margaritabokusumina.blogspot.com 💻puedes seguirme también en youtube, fb (2 perfiles, uno más usado que el otro, y una página de autora), en twitter y soundcloud 🎤(otros 2 perfiles, uno de ellos con más de 30 grabaciones en español, inglés y francés macarrónico)📲 #margaritabokusumina #creativemind #artrevolutionary #collectivebrainx #spanishartist #masmujeresdeizquierdasypobresenlasaltasesferas #escritora #agencialiteraria #editorial #culturainquieta  #literaryagency #editor #publisher @culturainquieta  #peoplemagazine #visualcreations #agenteliterario #selfpublished #postpunk #femalewriter #metoo #blogger #weremember

text:
i don’t know @lewishowes personally. however i did buy his book “the mask of masculinity” for my husband fred. not that my husband needs it because he has integrity. .
i appreciate and have admired how mr howes has shared his story of his childhood trauma and have learned so much from his interviews. ⭐️
recently some women have come forward to share their experiences with lewis who acted out inappropriately. he says they are lying. sometimes we do things that we are not aware of or how it could impact others negatively. ⭐️
wouldn’t it be nice to use this as an opportunity to learn and seek within? ⭐️
why would these women come forward? they make their own money on their own and are doing just fine.
⭐️
they are coming forward to share their truth. their experiences and concerns  an awareness that needs to have light shed on. ⭐️
while mr howe’s pr team are calling it out as lies etc wouldn’t it be nice instead if after some deep reflection he could just simply take responsibility and own it? ⭐️
think about it. when you admit wrongdoing or hurting others - it forces you to take off that “mask of masculinity” and get in touch with your feminine side. your intuition. your sensibility. your inner child. ⭐️
there is no shame in coming out and apologizing and taking a good look at oneself.
⭐️
what a great opportunity to come forward and apologize publicly. ⭐️
that way - he would not only come clean but he would earn much more respect and be rewarded with much growth and learning to become a better person. ⭐️
i’m cheering you on lewis. to do the right thing. ⭐️
congrats on your 6th year podcast anniversary. maybe the next episode could be about having a dialogue with these women coming forward to help heal the situation and so many people. ⭐️
don’t miss this opportunity to make it right bro. .
.

text:
happy friday instafam!

reminder that tomorrow begins my 10 weeks series on how to fully love self after trauma!

i’m kicking off the series with a quick chat on the sensuality of self care!🥰💕🥰 i will be hosting this series on my facebook wellness with candice page every saturday at 12 noon (pst) for the next 10 weeks!!🙏
come watch me live and catch some juicy stuff about me and my journey through trauma. 😊

learn how i can help you navigate the choppy waters of recovery and reclaim your personal power, sexual freedom and happiness!

learn how to use the struggles you’ve endured as the power to stand tall and proud in your life, embrace the uniqueness of you and thrive!

make yourself matter first and enjoy the peace & empowerment that self love creates!

text:
currently struggling with this freezing weather and wishing it was as pretty out there as in this photo.  anyone else over winter? ugh ❄️🥶
.
the town is apparently suffering rampant cases of flu, strep, conjuntivitis and stomach flu 🤧🤒😷🤢 i cannot diffuse enough immune supporting thieves essential oils blend, and i’m religiously rolling it on my kids’ spines, bottoms of feet and behind their ears at bedtime and right before they walk out the door to school 🏫 bye bye germs! 🙅‍♀️i’m so happy i have these tools to help us get through the season 🙏🏻 they’ve not been sick since i welcomed oils into our home, four months and counting... knock knock, knock.. 🌿
.
speaking of natural things.  if you’re looking for a great organic wine, i’m obsessed with @domainebousquet pinot noir reserve 2016 🌱🍇 made with 100% pinot noir grapes and aged for 10 months in french oak and 6 months in bottle.  color is super dark, medium body with well balanced acidity (my favorite style of red) 🤗 plums and ripe red fruit come forward in the nose and linger around in the palate, with a touch of coffee and toast from the oak.  i’m super into pinot noirs for a while now, this organic pinot is a good one to try 📝
.
happy #winewednesday! 🍷
.

text:
in the context of two major political stories as of this past week - obviously the nation wide federal government shutdowndown, and then another story that garnered an unbelievable explosion of reactionary and partisan politics regarding conflicts during the indigenous peoples march and the right to life march in dc this last weekend - i want to share a story of a nuanced interaction between a “liberal hollywood elite” public figure and what could potentially be considered a “right-wing troll.” it’s a reminder that the idea that we are so different is perpetuated by those who would see dissent and chaos reign. in reality people who actually share hardships, relate on issues, and have empathy for each other as individuals are far more common. good on @pattonoswalt and thank you for being an example to the rest of us who may be tempted to dehumanize people we see as having ideas other than our own. this also continues to highlight our issues of lack of livable wages, employees without collective bargaining power, and people without access to affordable healthcare.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
my proudest accomplishment in my life is getting my wings 4 years ago. i did it all on my own, without the help of anyone. i worked the same job for years even though i was very unhappy at times. i saved enough money so i didn’t have to take loans. i started my job at age 20 and within a few months i was sexually assaulted by a coworker. of course i never told anyone because i knew nothing would ever happen. but i didn’t stop working towards my dream.
in 6 weeks i flew 100hrs in 2014. these last 4 years i’ve flown about the same amount, got my faa commercial license  and hopefully soon i’ll be able to fly more though. #pilotlife #femalepilot #wings #pilot #commercialpilot #metoo

text: for those following along, we hope you enjoy part ii of episode 1, which may be confusing, so let me explain. each episode is a two-part episode. the first part is book review, and the second part is bringing topics from our book discussions out to the community.  in this podcast, we ask people in our community what they think about feminism.  is if for everyone as bell hooks claims?  do they identify as feminists, and if not, why?  what’s holding women back in the south?  is it fear, lack of support, lack of knowledge, confusion about the word, or is it the culture here?  listen to what women and men of all generations had to say.  subscribe to our podcast and visit our website femmsouth.com.  let us know what you think.  #femmsouth #feministpodcast #southernwomenreading #feminist #womenempowerment #women #womensupportingwomen #womensmarch #metoo #womeninmedia

text_retweet:
this is brilliant!👌 u may need to read the caption below to understand the videos better.

@nomore234ng(@repost_via_instant) what if law enforcement talked to people who have been robbed the same way they often treat people who have been sexually assaulted?

a new video written and directed by cynthia kao shows how absurd common responses to sexual assault allegations seem within the context of a robbery.

in the video, two police officers question a man about a laptop stolen from his home and continually suggest that the robbery was his fault — a nod to the victim-blaming so common in sexual assault cases. “flashing your goods for all the world to see? kinda sounds like you were asking for it,” one cop says when the man says his laptop was in front of a window. 
the officers also ask if the victim had been drinking question the “lack of evidence,” and tell the robbed man that filing a report will only cause more trouble. sexual assault survivors commonly hear these questions from police officers, which in turn discourages them from charging their assailants or even reporting the assault in the first place.

we wouldn’t blame someone for becoming a laptop-theft victim — don’t assault survivors deserve the same? - huffington post  #speakout #nomore #timesup #justice #metoo #endsexualassault #stopvictimblaming #supportingsurvivors #whyyoushouldreport

text:
c'etait-l'amour(dooooooooooog), 45x35 cm, 2011 
some times you just want to meet people in calm nightly dead end streets. hypothetical spoken: if there would be any reason today for me getting a gift i would love to settle some open account. in germany there are a lot of old white men. they got everything for no reason. they never have worked or created something, they are chauvinists, they never show guts, you can smell their frustration but they are in pretty high positions. in germany is no debate about #metoo it just continues. they just continue. 
when night falls they’ll find me out there.

text:
#flashback: 🔮 2018 i broke the spell. i spoke up. i started sharing parts of my story with videos & poetry. it was one of those most challenging things i’ve done, yet one of the most empowering.
__
one of the common side effects of abuse & trauma in survivors is the tendency to feel guilty & shame for other people’s violent behavior. we tend to feel responsible, unworthy & deserving of the violence & bullying.
__
we also tend to minimize our pain because others minimize us and have trained us to minimize ourselves.
__
i share my words to let others know you can heal through it, one step at a time. also to let you know you have nothing to be ashamed about. you are not to blame for the violent acts others have done to you or do to you ever.
__
i still have much to heal through, sometimes still struggle with ptsd, grief & anxiety. my loving support team helps me through it & so does honoring my truth & being gentle with myself when strong feelings arise. 
__
i’ve come so far & i’m here to serve as a reminder of the divine beauty, strength & intelligence that lives within you. you are powerful & needed in this world.
__
love, kat. 💜
__
#beseen #beheard #betrue #belove

text:
when docs sexually violate patients
first of a three-part series on physicians who abuse patients and the institutions that enable them
although the so-called #metoo movement got its start from allegations against hollywood mogul harvey weinstein in late 2017, victims of sexual abuse -- in the church, in the locker room, in the workplace, and, yes, in the exam room -- had already begun to speak up and demand accountability.
and while media coverage has tended to focus on the individual perpetrators, it's clear that there is more to the problem than just a few "bad apples." in this new medpage today series, we explore the background to sexual assault committed by physicians, and look at some of the systems that enable abuse and others that try to prevent it.
