text:
it’s over! the shutdown is over. for now... all that. for what? he achieved nothing! except needlessly and callously punishing the public — and — showing us all who’s really in charge in #washingtondc.
thank you #nancypelosi for standing up against our wannabe-bully-in-chief and keeping the focus where it should be: on the 800,000+ federal workers who have been missing multiple paychecks [including some legally required to still work] and countless other americans who are feeling the residual effects of this painful and dumb #trumpshutdown. out of touch and just plain cruel. but, why exactly was our government shutdown over american taxpayers paying for the wall — when #mexico is supposed to be paying for the wall? i don't give a crap about his fan’s spins and interpretations of what he meant to say, or what he really means… he said: "i will build a great wall -- and nobody builds walls better than me, believe me --and i'll build them very inexpensively. i will build a great, great wall on our southern border, and i will make mexico pay for that wall. mark my words." words…marked. he was very clear and specific. he even put it in writing! he wants money for his stupid wall?…it's going to have to be in pesos. end of discussion. #democrats now control the house and will put forth sensible legislation to benefit the people of this country. and, for the first time, will conduct real congressional oversight of #trump…his life will now [and deservedly so] become a virtual and perpetual deep colonoscopy…the saudis. abuse of power. corruption. ethics. kavanaugh. tax returns. obstruction of justice. #russia….you name it…we'll really start getting to the bottom of it…all! to save #america we must hold to account the inept, corrupt and amoral unindicted co-conspirator in the oval office: #illegitimate #failingpresident #donaldtrump. #lovetrumpshate #nevertrump #msnbc #foxnews #cnn #journalism #moveon #trumpprotest #notmypresident #politics #journalism #indivisible #makeamericagreatagain #womensmarch #crazytown #metoo #bluewave #maga

text:
take a deep breath.
•
do you ever feel so overwhelmed you don’t have time to slow down? or do you ever feel so overwhelmed you cannot get started. overwhelm. it can be so hard on our bodies. our bodies were not meant to carry such weight so don’t beat yourself up. take a deep breath. breathing in this blend can be so helpful. it’s one of my favorite blends to create for friends because i know relief is around the corner for them. i pray over each roller. prayer + oils—wonderful tools in this life i hope you too have in your toolbox. i also hope you’ll share your story. your struggles are personal to you; they’re purposeful. someone needs to hear you say #metoo.
•
the pinterest made famous “xanax blend” for a 5ml roller:
15 drops valor
15 drops stress away
15 drops lavender
15 drops patchouli
10 drops vetiver
top with carrier oil

•
•
•

text:
rp  @aussiefarms david littleproud mp, the federal minister for agriculture, has refused our invitation to debate whether modern animal farming is ethical. the national farmers federation claims these places (thousands of them) don't even exist. this is what they're trying to hide. 
consumers have a right to know that this is what they're paying for when they purchase meat, dairy and eggs. 
see more (much more) at www.watchdominion.com and https://maps.aussiefarms.org.au, and make up your own mind. 
littleproud and the nff continue trying to frame this as an issue of farmer safety, despite the fact that in 40 years of activists investigating farms and slaughterhouses, there has not been a single incident of violence towards farmers, workers, or their families. 
farmers are not afraid of their safety from peaceful, non-violent activists. they're afraid of their customers being able to see past the marketing slogans of "free range", "higher welfare" and "humane slaughter". this industry is afraid of finally being held accountable. #respectlife #loveanimals #letthembe #theirlivesmatter #lovethemall #animallovers #animalkingdom #familyiseverything #savetheocean #savetheearth #peaceandlove #govegan #crueltyfree #environment #environmentalist #planetearth #metoo #wildlife #wildlife_perfection #animalshaverights #proteina #babyanimals #donttakeourplanetforgranted

text:
thank you @pilatesstylemag for featuring my words, story, + mission in your current issue. for all of us who have been silenced by shame, and for the comfort of others, the opportunity to have just a bit of our story heard gives us a lot of life. my intuition fell in love with pilates before my mind knew why. pilates didn’t give me back the friends and connections i lost because i was raped, but it incrementally gave me back my body, and it gave me new friends (whom i cherish so deeply). we brush over the term “contrology” as a relic, but when your control is taken from you, this term holds hope. my instructors at true pilates ny, who trained me, held hope for me as they showed me my body was mine. now i am continuing to do the same for others like me, who need their body back, need their hope in place, and need a life lived not locked in past trauma, but lived firmly in the present and unafraid of the future. @pilatesstylemag : my gratitude reaches no limit.
.
.
.
.

text:
not my illustration, please do take credit if it’s yours. just trying to get the info out there, especially for those, like me, working with the body-mind (which is actually one thing, called 𝙮𝙤𝙪 ). notice in the illustration, ptsd’s (or ptsi, as some call it - new to me) effect on the brain stem. this is the oldest, most primitive part of the brain. it regulates the body’s automatic functions, like breathing. the focus on breathing in pilates, while yes, strengthening the core + detoxifying the body, also aids in homeostasis: sweet relief to the traumatized, whose nervous system has likely gone haywire.
.
liz koch (the psoas book) advises to “guide” breathing, rather than “teach” breathing, as it is a “natural process” and need not be taught. therefore, suggesting that a client just notice their breath can be simply effective and revelatory.
.
a side note: this illustration states that 94% of sa survivors develop ptsd immediately following the attack - true. for some survivors, the ptsd dissipates over time, due to therapy, a solid support system, and/or luck. for others, it stays. maybe not bearing the severity of its initial symptoms, but it stays. it has stayed for me, despite pouring my resources into eradicating it. ptsd has lessened its grip on me, but i expect i will need to regulate it for the rest of my life. so, sometimes, while lying on the reformer, you’ll see me not moving, but just noticing my breath.
.
❤️ to fellow survivors and those who serve them.
.
.

text:
поверну время назад и скажу семилетней девочке машеньке. ⠀
у тебя будет не лучшее время в детстве, но родители всегда будут стараться  тебе дать лучшего и всегда прислушиваться к твоим задумкам. а самое главное они тебя будут поддерживать и любить. у тебя будет многое и даже долгожданный велик 🚲
⠀
детка, ты быстро повзрослеешь и будешь принимать сложные решения сама. брать ответственность, делать первые шаги в неизвестное с которыми сама справишься.

text: my first tattoo. i am very satisfied on how it came out. here’s a little bit of why i chose this word and the placement of it. i am in a good place to finally be comfortable with my body and my life. if you look closely you can see a scar where the i and o are. i gave myself that scar when i was younger. at that point in my life i was in a dark place where i felt there was no way out. certain events in my life made me feel worthless, alone, scared, ashamed, and i went through them on my own. i’ve carried these secrets for many years and they have been destroying me little by little without me even knowing. i have been bitter and angry for too long. it wasn’t until recently that i came to this realization that it’s okay to be angry but not stay angry. it’s okay to feel all these emotions but to not let the past interfere with my future. i am ready to finally forgive those who have hurt me and to finally let go of the pain. i have scars to remind me how far i’ve come. i have scars to show me i’ve made it through what i considered no hope. so i chose a word to put over my scar. i didn’t want to hide it or cover it up. i wanted to look at the scar and the word i chose to tell myself yes i went through a lot but i’m here and i’m bodacious! this word to me is strong, bold, beauty, amazing, etc. i am comfortable with me. i am bodacious, i am amazing, i am lovely, i am strong, i am bold. i know there are going to be times where i am not going to feel all these wonderful things about myself but that’s okay. i just know now that i can’t stay in that negative state of mind. i can’t let myself go back to those dark times. i will remind myself to be bodacious! i am happy to share a little bit of myself to you. thank you for reading. 💋💋💕💕🖤🖤🙌👌🤟💪😁 #bodacious #metoo #forgive #comfortable #tattoos #weareallbeautiful #iamnoangel #smalltattoos #onewordtattoos #happytobeme #thereisnoonelikeme #iamgoingtobeokay #excitingmoment
name: Abby Martinez

text:
in an interview with bloomberg news, @senjoniernst (r-iowa) said that she was raped while in college, making her one of the highest-profile women in congress to share an experience with sexual assault. ernst said she had entered into a relationship with someone who was “physically and sexually abusive,” and alleges that he raped her at his home when she attended iowa state university. she told bloomberg that she called the campus sexual assault hotline and ended the relationship but did not report the incident to police. “i was embarrassed,” she said of her decision not to tell. “i didn’t know how to explain it. i was so humiliated. and i’m a private person, when it comes to those things.”
•
the senator, who was elected in 2014 adds a republican voice to the national conversation about sexual assault, also known as #metoo. “i didn’t want to share it with anybody, and in the era of hashtag-metoo survivors, i always believed that every person is different and they will confront their demons when they’re ready. and i was not ready,” ernst said. but this week, court documents from her divorce became public, alleging physical and emotional abuse by her ex-husband, gail ernst, putting her private life in the spotlight. the documents were quickly sealed. (photo by cliff owen / ap; illustration by @thelilynews)

text:
a short meditation on the virgin mary, the woman that all generations will call "blessed". she carried the unborn christ-child, the everlasting god as a fetus. to the great delight of the #metoo movement, we see her consent being critical and valuable to god's redemptive work; to the dismay of the #prochoice movement, the incarnation of god gives infinite worth to the life of the unborn. in our nation, it would be legal and indeed heralded as virtuous for god with us to be killed in the womb of our blessed mother, crucified and abandoned before taking his first breath.

margaret sanger, the founder of planned parenthood, once said that children born to impoverished parents caused all that was wrong in the world. and yet, this child born to impoverished parents caused all that is good in the world to be realized, and all that is wrong to be overcome.

mary serves as an enigma to both conservatives and progressives, and yet, in the pregnancy of a teenage peasant living under a military dictatorship, the new world of the gospel breaks forth into our existence of death, oppression, and suffering. 
#theology #credimus #meditation #mary #blessedvirginmary #consent #metoo #prochoice #prolife #plannedparenthood #abortion #consistentlifeethic

text:
did she tell you about the time, 
where dementors filled in silences,
when the light was a kind of darkness a mortal couldn't percieve,
did she tell you about the time,
she finally cut too deep?

did you hear her cries for help
when in fear she shrieked,
or was it loud enough to make your knees too weak?

did you hear it from a whisper finding it's way in a crowd,
just as the drop of sweat trickles down your back in the scorching heat?

did you envision her bathing in her blood, 
as that voice led you to what she had done?
a cut too shallow,
a cut too deep,
a bunch of girls yelling "get up, you freak!" where you there? 
did you sit there? 
did you watch me?

where you the one who looked me in the eye,
as i found the voice i lost amid the song,
to finally
call out for help?
name: Writings Of An Unstable Mind

text: this is a little heavy for a friday, but here it goes. i’ve been thinking a lot about corruption within yoga and the world. (aka not everyone who does yoga is a good person part 2) it is clear from the ancient stories that misguided intentions lead to demonic actions at worst and unfortunate deeds at best. while we know that power and prowess isn’t the point of yoga just doing yoga won’t stop anyone from being cruel or unjust. most of us probably know not every person in yoga class is trustworthy, compassionate and moral, but there are also many stories about yogis who do their practices and austerities, achieve great power and are demons or simply not ethical beings (vasistha and mahishasura come to mind). these along with the #metoo movement -from which the yoga world is not exempt- are proof that aligning your chakras won’t necessarily align your values and actions. in ytt we used to say “just let the yoga take care of them” we thought that if an individual just did yoga they would become wonderful. in retrospect with modern postural yoga being what it is today, we were really just being nosy and then spiritually bypassing. it seems to me that any practice void of the commitment to truth you wish to manifest in the world is just gymnastics on a sticky mat. (and there isn’t anything wrong with that) and a practice that doesn’t bring you more in line with the truth and the vital self is much the same. power can be built regardless of intention. so can pretty asanas. you don’t even have to be a good person to spout off a dharma talk on vedanta, tantra, sankhya or any other wisdom tradition you connect with. so i personally checking in with myself and holding myself accountable. i’m going to try to share some of that with you folks going forward. whew! that was a lot. i hope you enjoy your friday! just another seeker in love with yoga and movement practice. #yogaeverywhere #yogainspiration #asana #phillyyoga #vinyasa #flow #yoginispirit #yogainternational #yogapartout #yoginisofinstagram #instayoga #sahajasoma #yogawithkayla #yogateacherlife #yogaeverydamnday #yogamama #yoga #yogini #yogateacher
name: Sahaja Soma, Yoga with Kayla

text:
#interraciallovestory  #loveislovestory™🏳️‍🌈 + #climateaction gender debate "eve n'god this female is not yet rated ™" opens  feb 1, 2019 for a one week run through feb 7, 2019.  the " #freshoffthegrid™ #handmade " new indie run, follows immediately after #thefavourite runs.
eve n'god this female is not yet rated ™  plays 3 shows a day, #dtla  @downtownindependent cinema :  251 s. main street, la  90012  ph. (213) 617- 1033 
the allegorical #avantgarde fairytale is described as “1 day in the epiphany of a 21st century girl, who kissed a girl ™ a lost+found virginity #fantasy bordering on polyamory ; a bittersweet romance in the key of rock n’ #soul ; an immersive  floating #scifi dream as global girl awakens to the legacy of herself.” the all-female crew production from actressauteur™  cali lili + her #sustainable #upcycled movie + music studio in #gentrification -torn venice beach canals with #oceanconservancy footage including a local octopus named "octavia" + other #sealife appearing unprompted 4 the lens during principal photography was made w 90% upcycled original costumes + sets farmersmarket items for "garden of eve" set.

text: not feeling today. or, i guess, feeling too much today. i thought i was making some progress in finding myself again, but fought with my husband, had an anxiety spike, argued with my kids, and now feel back at square one. i almost deleted this account too. my anxiety told me it was a ridiculous, childish, drama, diva idea to even create it in the first place. don't normal people just write in a journal, not needing or even wanting another soul to read their words? but, i've never actually felt heard before. not authentically anyway. so even if complete strangers are randomly scrolling past and read just one post, maybe i'm not invisible. maybe i can be unapologetically me. maybe i can take the masks off, for i have many. maybe i can start to honestly talk about the underlying issues and causes of my mental health status. maybe... #anxiety #depression #selflovenovice #selflove #itsaslowprocess #metoo #sexualabusesurvivor #unapologeticallyme #findingpeace

text:
häromdagen mötte jag en man i en bil. 
jag hade inte sett honom om han inte saktat in och framförallt om han inte böjt sig fram över passagerarsidan i sin bil och gett mig en utstuderad och yvig slängkyss.
jag som gick i egna tankar, med en god bok i lurarna och tittade på hur snön glittrade i trädgrenarna, kastades för ett ögonblick tillbaka i tiden. 
jag kastades för ett ögonblick tillbaka till tiden då jag levde tillsammans med denna man och hur jag efter alltför lång tid lyckades bryta mig loss. hur jag som en sista hjälp för att markera både för mig själv, honom och omvärlden, och med uppmuntran av ett polisbiträde anmälde honom för det som han utsatt mig för i den zon som ska vara trygg, vårt hem.
jag tänker att hans gest är en triumf som han vill visa upp, över att han till sist blev frikänd, nej, mer korrekt, inte kunde fällas eftersom bevisen inte var tillräckliga då ord stod mot ord och eftersom jag inte dokumenterat särskilt väl utan snarare mörkat, av skam för vad han utsatte mig och även mina barn för.
jag tänker att jag inte ska skriva om detta på mitt öppna konto, eftersom jag vet att han läser, och jag vägrar att göra de anonymt, att gömma mig. jag tänker att jag inte ska skriva eftersom han kan ta det som en vinst, att jag såg honom och att det störde mig.
så idag, när jag lyssnar på stina wollters bok ”i denna kropp” bestämmer jag mig ändå för att skriva. 
jag tänker att om något ska ändras i samhället måste vi alla göra det tillsammans, och då måste vi också våga tala om det skamliga, våga erkänna vad som händer. hur kvinnor, oftast, blir utsatta av män, oftast. och hur framförallt män, men även kvinnor skyddar, ja faktiskt sanktionerar ett dåligt beteende. jag skriver män och kvinnor som en generalisering utan att för den skull vara omedveten om att alla inte faller inom den kategorin. jag har dock landat i att de flesta sorterar på det sättet och att alla som faller utanför mansnormen riskerar att förtryckas. 
vad vill jag då?
jag vill att alla, även "alla män" tar detta på allvar. detta är inte färdigt förrän vi alla slutar att blunda, slutar att sanktionera, och börjar markera att mäns våld inte är okej, i någon form. 
#metoo

text:
victims of bullying and sexual exploitation are more likely to suffer a lower quality of life than those with current heart disease, diabetes, and mental illnesses.  this is the conclusion of an australian study of some 3,000 persons of all ages and socioeconomic levels.

the researchers used the presence of multiple self-destructive behaviors including smoking and binge eating as signs of troubled lives.  those who had been bullied and sexually abused were twice as likely as controls to be problem smokers, 3 times more likely to have an eating disorder, and four times more likely to be depressed.

bullying, both physical and now electronic, is becoming epidemic, and more sexual abuse is discovered yearly in synch with the #metoo movement.  if these plagues affect you or yours, combat them vigorously knowing the impact they’ll have on health and wellness.

bullying, sexual abuse, metoo, smoking, eating disorder, depression, health news, health tips
#bullying #sexualabuse #metoo #smoking #eatingdisorder #depression #healthnews #healthtips

david alejandro gonzález-chica, julio licinio, michael musker, mali wong, jacqueline bowden, phillipa hay, catherine chittleborough, nigel stocks. bullying and sexual abuse and their association with harmful behaviours, antidepressant use and health-related quality of life in adulthood: a population-based study in south australia. bmc public health, 2019; 19 (1) doi: 10.1186/s12889-018-6367-8

text:
4/26 weeks of feminism! we made it an entire month 💖💖 this week the most intelligent and strong sophie gives an incredible perspective on the correlation between feminism and veganism. i loved talking with her earlier this week over a nice cup of coffee and getting to hear her wonderful take on being a women and outspoken in the fight for equality. love her and love her meaning of feminism! proud of you beautiful 🌸☀️
“‘darkness cannot drive out darkness; only light can do that. hate cannot drive out hate; only love can do that.’ feminism, simply stated, is leading by example. we are all taking part in a social movement, a true paradigm shift in our cultural systems. each of us have the power to decide which path leading to the shift we will choose. 
i am a feminist, therefore i am an animal activist. i see the exploitation of animals that parallels our treatment of women. we oppress animals just as we oppress women. dairy cows and egg-laying hens are used as reproductive servants, and in that mirror, i see the objectification of women and ownership of their reproductive rights. our social constructs support a chauvinistic and oppressive culture, inclusive of our food systems. let us turn on our spotlights, lead by example, and drive out the darkness of our society. women’s rights are human rights are animal rights. which path leading to the paradigm shift will you choose? that of darkness or the path of light?”

text:
when we choose a path, we can't see past the immediate bend in the road and we have to take a step out in faith. it is exhilarating not to know where it leads but sometimes that initial excitement can turn to apprehension or doubt.
i've come to realize my life is quite like a hiking trail, in that, there are periods of time that the scenery is beautifully lush with a fairly easy trail beneath my feet and glorious oak trees shading my journey but then there are forks in the road and i must choose which direction to hike. niether direction is bad, they each offer their own set of challenges and beauties. 
the terrain at times is easy to navigate only to turn the corner and no longer be protected by the shade of my beloved oak trees and i must travel on harsh, rocky, hot, dusty and oft times perilous trails that are so narrow that i have to put one foot in front of the other and one slip can cause major injury. 
i have found that on the rough trails i am tested to my limits. my sanity is tested. self doubt creeps in where i cannot afford it to.  switchbacks taunt me, i've traveled so far yet i can clearly see where i was miles ago.  frustration sets in, how can i have hiked so far but not gained much in elevation??
i push forward. continuing on through the pain, through the exhaustion, through the grief, knowing that the peak must be near... or at least go until i can no longer push through.
cresting a ridge is exhilarating....there is no other feeling like it...to be rewarded with a view unlike any other. 
such is my life. full of imense pain and obstacles to persevere through but also so enjoyable after i choose to press forward. and  weither it be my ego, my stubbornness or hope driving my decisions, i continue on my path and embrace the journey. ...

....
...

an english satire class from @saintgertrudeva joined us in the #rvaforum student room on saturday for our program with tina fey. it sounds like they had a great time! 
our student room is made possible in part by your support of the krueger fund. learn more and donate at richmond forum.org/give. 
#repost @saintgertrudeva
・・・
last saturday, a group of our students had the opportunity to hear from tina fey when she appeared at the richmond forum. tina joined our girls in the student room before the presentation and answered questions about her comedy, the #metoo movement, and her experience at snl. english department chair jenny watkins was exceptionally proud when everyone was asked if they knew what satire was and everyone of our students raised their hands. it was a fun -- and funny -- evening!

text: i answered a question i get asked all the time by other survivors, “with only body memories, do i still have moments of doubt about my trauma?” and i wrote what it’s like to be fully certain of my survivorship while also experiencing moments of doubt, and how those two things aren’t actually in conflict, but rather that’s just how trauma works. i feel such relief to have this story out, while also feeling the exhaustion of being so vulnerable in my writing. i chose to write this because i have the privilege of being validated and affirmed by survivors who message me everyday, and everyone else deserves to be able to feel that way too. link in bio.  #ptsd #cptsd #metoo #csa cover📷 by @mariahmirandaphoto

text:
social and sexual abuse drive substantial health decline

vidcast: https://youtu.be/zg9qzeod8iy

victims of bullying and sexual exploitation are more likely to suffer a lower quality of life than those with current heart disease, diabetes, and mental illnesses.  this is the conclusion of an australian study of some 3,000 persons of all ages and socioeconomic levels.

the researchers used the presence of multiple self-destructive behaviors including smoking and binge eating as signs of troubled lives.  those who had been bullied and sexually abused were twice as likely as controls to be problem smokers, 3 times more likely to have an eating disorder, and four times more likely to be depressed.

bullying, both physical and now electronic, is becoming epidemic, and more sexual abuse is discovered yearly in synch with the #metoo movement.  if these plagues affect you or yours, combat them vigorously knowing the impact they’ll have on health and wellness.

social and sexual abuse drive substantial health decline

vidcast: https://youtu.be/zg9qzeod8iy

victims of bullying and sexual exploitation are more likely to suffer a lower quality of life than those with current heart disease, diabetes, and mental illnesses.  this is the conclusion of an australian study of some 3,000 persons of all ages and socioeconomic levels.

the researchers used the presence of multiple self-destructive behaviors including smoking and binge eating as signs of troubled lives.  those who had been bullied and sexually abused were twice as likely as controls to be problem smokers, 3 times more likely to have an eating disorder, and four times more likely to be depressed.

bullying, both physical and now electronic, is becoming epidemic, and more sexual abuse is discovered yearly in synch with the #metoo movement.  if these plagues affect you or yours, combat them vigorously knowing the impact they’ll have on health and wellness.

text:
¿ustedes se dieron cuenta que la frase final del discurso de mike pence para venezuela fue: “vayan con dios”? es la frase final de la película “the magnificent seven” que fue estrenada originalmente en 1.960 y la nueva versión salió en el 2.016... una aldea pobre en méxico es atacada periódicamente por comida y suministros por una pandilla de bandidos liderada por calvera (eli wallach 1.960). después de la última redada, durante la cual los bandidos matan a un aldeano, los líderes de la aldea deciden que ya han tenido suficiente, y por consejo del anciano de la aldea (vladimir sokoloff 1.960), deciden responder. tomando los pocos objetos de valor que tiene el pueblo, tres aldeanos viajan a una ciudad dentro de la frontera de los estados unidos con la esperanza de intercambiar armas y allí consiguen el apoyo de 7 norteamericanos que vienen a la aldea, los ayudan a prepararse para el próximo ataque de los bandidos y les enseñan cómo defenderse, los liberan de calvera y sus secuaces... ¿casualidades? no lo creo... para despedirse de los aldeanos, luego de ser liberados, les dicen: “vayan con dios”
🙏🏻
#libertad #god #venezuelalibre #prayforvenezuela #freedomvenezuela #freedom #venezuelafreedom #usa #godblessamerica #mikepence #themagnificentseven #estamosunidosve
@christian_sba @vp #texas #tx

¿ustedes se dieron cuenta que la frase final del discurso de mike pence para venezuela fue: “vayan con dios”? es la frase final de la película “the magnificent seven” que fue estrenada originalmente en 1.960 y la nueva versión salió en el 2.016... una aldea pobre en méxico es atacada periódicamente por comida y suministros por una pandilla de bandidos liderada por calvera (eli wallach 1.960). después de la última redada, durante la cual los bandidos matan a un aldeano, los líderes de la aldea deciden que ya han tenido suficiente, y por consejo del anciano de la aldea (vladimir sokoloff 1.960), deciden responder. tomando los pocos objetos de valor que tiene el pueblo, tres aldeanos viajan a una ciudad dentro de la frontera de los estados unidos con la esperanza de intercambiar armas y allí consiguen el apoyo de 7 norteamericanos que vienen a la aldea, los ayudan a prepararse para el próximo ataque de los bandidos y les enseñan cómo defenderse, los liberan de calvera y sus secuaces... ¿casualidades? no lo creo... para despedirse de los aldeanos, luego de ser liberados, les dicen: “vayan con dios”
🙏🏻

text:
richard b. cohen of fisherbroyles explains what workplace bullying is pretty clearly. most of us know it immediately when we see or experience it, but don’t always know what to do it about it.

when bullying goes unreported, the offender usually repeats the behavior and management is often unaware of the issue.

don’t stay silent if you witness disruptive or harmful behavior at work.  you can anonymously report it directly to the offender’s manager at www.warble.work.

text:
throughout the committee hearing, several republican senators including ted cruz and thom tillis pointed to the obama campaign’s use of facebook data, to highlight the fact that such practices are bipartisan.

however, people who downloaded the obama campaign app were aware they were using a political app. by contrast, the data obtained by cambridge analytica was obtained via a personality quiz application whose users had no idea their data would be used by a political campaign.

cambridge analytica improperly obtained the personal information of millions of facebook users to build profiles of us voters in order to target them with personalised political advertisements, via a related uk-based entity called scl elections.
.
- we exploited facebook to harvest millions of people’s profiles, said wylie in march. - and built models to exploit what we knew about them and target their inner demons. that was the basis the entire company was built on.

wylie has previously told mps at a british select committee that the eu referendum was won through fraud after vote leave allegedly used a network of companies to get round election spending laws. he said he thought there “could have been a different outcome had there not been, in my view, cheating”. he also met privately with house democrats in april, but wednesday’s hearing was his first public appearance before us lawmakers.

olivia solon
the guardian

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
i have had the most amazing message today from a woman in our #speakoutsisterhood group on fb telling me how much it is helping her in her path to recovery.

in putting my head above the parapet and sharing my story of over coming abuse i wanted to inspire others to acknowledge their past and begin the road to heal, and most importantly not feel alone.

my mission has only just begun, but to know that it's helping other's fills my heart with joy.

#survivor #metoo #warrior #timetospeakup #campaigner #nomoresilence #resilience #itsnosecret #speakoutsisterhood

very proud to be sharing this work created in collaboration with @micaela_mamede for her awe inspiring choreography performance at gibney dance, this is #maria2018. produced and performed by an ensemble of non-us immigrant women and allies, maria tells the all too common story of violence and silence immigrant women face. this whole project was made possible by micaela and her unwavering visual mission to share her own voice. she's since gained the support of the #healmetoo festival, a grassroots foundation working to heal victims of sexual violence by funding creative, therapeutic outlets for victims. please join us at the first ever nyc heal me too festival march 27-april 19, 2019. to learn more about their work, please follow @micaela_mamede and @healmetoofest and visit www.healmetoofest.com #metoo #womenshistorymonth #intimatepartnerviolence #healing - makeup by @batamakeup and cast: #danutapetrow-sek #emilyteller #hayetmoutfi, #krishnawashburn #malaikacambridge #maluavalos #mariasek #micaelamamede and #pearlbhatnagar - thank you ladies. xo

text:
toonews 25 january 2019
“ o mundo está ficando chato”. eu acho. ld, minha amiga, também acha. ela está triste. eu, cansada. “politicamente corretos” são chatos. veganos são chatos. lgbts são chatos. #metoo é chato. peta é chato e mais, milhares de grupos, associações, entidades e, sei lá mais o que, são chatos. todos surgiram para enfrentar o status quo (eu estou velha, só os velhos falam isso! ah, velhos também são chatos!) porém, acabaram caindo na cruel mesmice de quem tanto se propuseram combater. e, o pior, fazendo e causando o mesmo mal. william sitchell, veterano e badalado crítico gastronômico inglês, e, editor chefe há 20 anos da revista de comida da chiquíssima rede de supermercados waitrose, perdeu seu emprego porque uma jornalista novata e vegana, achou sua brincadeira, feita numa troca de e-mails privados, (“ir matando os veganos, um a um, a cada dia”) ofensiva e “ vitriolítica” (dicionário, dicionário!) ela disse que ficou zangada e, jogou na internet!!!( ficou zangada!!!) sitchell, foi, imediatamente, bombardeado por milhões, sim, milhões de e-mails de veganos tão raivosos que não teve outra saída, a não ser, a sua própria. demitiu-se! ”asse seu bebê no forno”, “sua mulher será estuprada“ “sua casa será revistada e você preso, pois deve ser um serial killer”, são algumas das mensagens que estes adoráveis defensores dos pobres e sofredores animais, mandaram para ele. um mal irreparável. a polarização das idéias e a hipocrisia de ambos os lados. tá chato. todos são os donos da verdade. todos têm razão. sem comentários. sem piadinhas. sem paquera. sem nada. qualquer assunto vira um “ case”. tabu. cerceamento de todos os tipos do “politicamente incorreto”. anedotas de português, paquera no trabalho, assobio de peão de obra, dizer que o fulano é “ bicha” e a fulana é “ sapatão”, mandar o cozinheiro deixar a carne bem “sangrenta”, matar ratos. a lista é enorme. não pode! a vida tem que ser chata. o mundo tem gente demais e governos de menos. tudo igual desde o começo: é o fim! extremos. todavia, a gente continua igual. só nasce e morre. e o resto..., é chato! a outra news??? ah, é chata! ukilike🇬🇧🇧🇷

text:
arizona'da bitkisel hayatta hamile kadın vakası ve #metoo hareketinin sessiz kurbanları 
abd'nin arizona eyaletinde 10 yıldır bitkisel hayatta bulunan bir hastanın doğum yaptığı haberi tüm dünyada büyük bir şok yarattı.
bu olay, cinsel saldırıya maruz kalma riski yüksek olan kadınların başlarına gelenlerin bir örneği. ayrıca kendilerini taciz edenlere karşı fiziksel olarak ses çıkarması mümkün olmayanlar da tacize karşı küresel bir kampanya olan #metoo hareketinin bir parçasını oluşturuyor.
bitkisel hayattayken 29 aralık'ta bir erkek çocuğu dünyaya getiren kadının kimliği açıklanmadı. phoenix kentinde bulunan hacienda healthcare adlı bir bakımevinde kalan hasta, 10 yıldır bitkisel hayatta bulunuyordu.
bakımevinde çalışan 36 yaşındaki erkek hemşire nathan sutherland hakkında cinsel saldırı ve korumasız bir yetişkine yönelik suiistimal suçlamalarından dava açıldı.
burada çalışanlar daha önce yaptıkları açıklamalarda, doğum başlayana kadar hastanın hamile olduğunu fark etmediklerini söyledi.

text:
via @fayobserver: gaston county’s district attorney says a woman who claimed to be beaten with a hammer tuesday by an estranged husband fabricated the entire story.

locke bell said when amanda biggers spoke to gastonia police detectives in a follow-up interview thursday, “none of her stories made sense.” “it’s like when she says, ‘my husband was behind me on this occasion.’ he had a(n) (ankle monitor) that he was wearing,” bell said.

bell said there were several other inconsistencies in her story, and that one of his assistant district attorneys was present for the interrogation, when biggers “finally admitted that she was making it all up and said she might be making it up because of ptsd.” gastonia police arrested jurmario biggers on tuesday and charged him with violating a domestic violence protection order by using a deadly weapon and assault with a deadly weapon inflicting serious injury.

bell said thursday he is dismissing those charges. “we always have to make sure we protect women who are victims, but we also have a duty to make sure it’s the truth when it comes out in court,” bell said.
